"/> No I don't think it's offensive, just as long as the dealer is asked
beforehand ... &quot;excuse me but would you mind awfully if I took a couple
of shots&quot; ... summit like that.

Think it would be offensive, well slightly rude, if someone popped into
another dealers shop and started to fire off rolls of film just out of
the blue, then buggered off without saying a word or a thank you.

But I must admit, it would be fun after they took the shots and punted
the item all over the place, got a real good &quot;promised&quot; price then came
back to buy the item .... it would be fun to say .. &quot;oh sorry that's sold
now, he who hesitates is lost&quot; ... or summit like that ... course it's
not sold and is still setting there bold as brass.

Tell the truth, we have a couple of annoying guys that go around the
trade, never buy anything unless they have a sure-fired punter already
lined up. They will eyeball something, maybe photograph it, then go off
trying to tout it around the trade, telling all sorts of porky-pies, then
comeback in a few days later and will start with a big haggling match. In
a case like that, I would get a kick out telling them it's sold ..even if
it's not sold .. Sure there's always another mug around the corner,
everything sell eventually so why spoil the fun in between.

....... one-upmanship is a great game to play, passes away the slow dark
winter months just after Christmas. ;&gt;))

Ronnie
