As the old saying goes, &quot;Don't wish for something; you might get it&quot; -
seems to be the case. I collect one narrow area, and with all the
outlets in New England, probably never spent more than a couple hundred
dollars per year, due to the fact that the items were not very
expensive, plus not that much turned up. With Ebay, my spending and
collection has grown at least ten-fold. In fact, through Ebay bought one
of my &quot;holy grail&quot; items: Sent the check, got the package, looked at the
item once and put it away in a carton with my other stuff. It wasn't the
price, but the method that makes it kind of dull now.

So, I think the fun is going away, but I am probably in the minority.
Nowadays, for most people collecting means putting in your order for the
latest Byer's or other collectible item at a local gift shop. Why not do
it on line?

